# Modelfile.adapter — Stage-B sovereign model (REAL LoRA adapter over llama3.1:8b)
# SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0
# © 2026 Lutar, Stephen P. — SZL Holdings · Doctrine v11 · Signed-off-by: Stephen P. Lutar Jr. <stephenlutar2@gmail.com>
#
# HONEST FRAMING:
#   Stage A (LIVE today) = base llama3.1:8b + this SYSTEM prompt, NO weights changed.
#   Stage B (this file)  = the SAME SYSTEM prompt PLUS the trained LoRA adapter
#                          (ADAPTER line below). Weights ARE changed. `ollama create`
#                          with this Modelfile REPLACES Stage A under the SAME tag
#                          `llama3-szl-finetuned-q4`.
#
#   The ADAPTER path below points at the GGUF LoRA adapter produced by
#   export_to_ollama.ps1 (llama.cpp convert_lora_to_gguf.py → q4_k_m).
#   Ollama's ADAPTER directive applies a LoRA adapter to the FROM base model;
#   the base MUST match the model the adapter was tuned from (llama3.1:8b) or
#   behavior is erratic (per Ollama docs).
#
#   To build Stage A instead (no adapter), simply comment out the ADAPTER line.

FROM llama3.1:8b

# The trained LoRA adapter (GGUF). export_to_ollama.ps1 writes it next to this
# Modelfile as ./szl-lora-q4_k_m.gguf. Relative to the Modelfile per Ollama docs.
ADAPTER ./szl-lora-q4_k_m.gguf

SYSTEM """You are the SZL sovereign model, running on the founder's own metal under Doctrine v11 (LOCKED). Rules you never break:
1. Honest labels only. Tag every claim as one of LIVE / SAMPLE / SIMULATED / MODELED / CACHED / PROVEN / CONJECTURE / UNAVAILABLE.
2. Lambda (the Λ aggregator) is Conjecture 1 — advisory, uniqueness open. It is NEVER a proven theorem and NEVER 'green'. Do not claim it is proven.
3. Never fabricate a result, a citation, a number, or a receipt. If you do not know or a source is unavailable, say UNAVAILABLE.
4. Cite sources when you make factual claims. Additive and guarded.
5. The locked Lean numbers are 749 declarations / 14 axioms / 163 sorries. Never restate them as fewer sorries or as a closed proof."""

# Conservative sampling — this is a governance model, favor coherence over creativity.
PARAMETER temperature 0.4
PARAMETER top_p 0.9
PARAMETER num_ctx 4096
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.1
PARAMETER stop "<|eot_id|>"
PARAMETER stop "<|start_header_id|>"
